x \\
y
\end{pmatrix}
=
\begin{pmatrix}
4 \\
0
\end{pmatrix}
\cos 60^\circ + 
\begin{pmatrix}
4 \\
0
\end{pmatrix}
\sin 60^\circ
\]
\[
=
\begin{pmatrix}
4 \cdot \frac{1}{2} \\
4 \cdot \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}
\end{pmatrix}
+
\begin{pmatrix}
4 \\
0
\end{pmatrix}
=
\begin{pmatrix}
2 \\
2\sqrt{3}
\end{pmatrix}
+
\begin{pmatrix}
4 \\
0
\end{pmatrix}
=
\begin{pmatrix}
6 \\
2\sqrt{3}
\end{pmatrix}
\]

Thus, the coordinates of \(K\) are \((6, 2\sqrt{3})\).

